WEBVTT

1
00:02:24.720 --> 00:02:25.840
Three more in here.

2
00:02:48.200 --> 00:02:49.020
You three.

3
00:02:49.540 --> 00:02:50.260
This one.

4
00:02:52.300 --> 00:02:53.280
Please. please.

5
00:02:54.600 --> 00:02:56.880
Our home. it's already crowded.

6
00:02:57.360 --> 00:02:58.860
There's 15.000 of us.

7
00:02:59.740 --> 00:03:01.140
I'm glad you only got three.

8
00:03:03.900 --> 00:03:05.600
Maybe crowded ain't so bad.

9
00:03:06.020 --> 00:03:06.680
Mind yourself.

10
00:03:08.030 --> 00:03:10.040
You don't like it going cop to Lord
Ormond.

11
00:03:10.980 --> 00:03:12.100
See what good it does you.

12
00:03:25.060 --> 00:03:28.640
It is only regarding the lodging
situation. my lord.

13
00:03:29.520 --> 00:03:31.760
You are unhappy with your lodging.
Lord Footeley?

14
00:03:32.210 --> 00:03:34.580
It is only that we are very fond of our
ancestral home.

15
00:03:34.580 --> 00:03:36.160
You are sleeping in our bedchamber.

16
00:03:37.200 --> 00:03:40.240
You bent the knee to the pretender
Rhaenyra Targaryen. did you not.

17
00:03:40.360 --> 00:03:40.940
Lady Footeley?

18
00:03:41.680 --> 00:03:42.260
We did.

19
00:03:43.780 --> 00:03:46.140
And mayhaps I should remind you that the
voyage of treason is death.

20
00:03:46.940 --> 00:03:48.460
We do not seek conflict. my lord.

21
00:03:48.840 --> 00:03:50.460
Tumbleton has no battlements.

22
00:03:51.080 --> 00:03:52.420
Our people know only trade.

23
00:03:52.620 --> 00:03:54.560
We never thought to see war.

24
00:03:55.350 --> 00:03:56.940
So you swore to her out of fear?

25
00:03:57.430 --> 00:03:59.500
We swore because she is the queen.

26
00:04:02.960 --> 00:04:03.840
Is she?

27
00:04:15.030 --> 00:04:16.700
Or is she a bitch with a dragon?

28
00:04:21.495 --> 00:04:24.580
My purpose is to restore the rightful line
to the Iron Throne.

29
00:04:26.180 --> 00:04:28.240
It follows from that that I must be well
rested.

30
00:04:30.130 --> 00:04:33.720
It follows from that that I must have
acceptable lodgings.

31
00:04:35.280 --> 00:04:39.720
I will ensure that my men remain on their
best behavior whilst in your town.

32
00:04:42.280 --> 00:04:47.800
Provided. of course. that you remain on
yours.

33
00:04:49.000 --> 00:04:49.920
See them out.

34
00:04:52.700 --> 00:04:53.260
Don't.

35
00:04:54.710 --> 00:04:57.720
When dealing with those beneath you.
you must be fair but firm.

36
00:04:57.720 --> 00:04:59.100
Yes. sir.

37
00:05:02.500 --> 00:05:03.340
By Prince.

38
00:05:03.780 --> 00:05:04.480
By Lord.

39
00:05:04.910 --> 00:05:09.020
A raven from Storm's End carrying more
excuses from Lord Boris Baratheon.

40
00:05:16.430 --> 00:05:19.550
That lack would seal the marriage pact
between Prince Heymund and one of his

41
00:05:20.200 --> 00:05:21.510
horse-faced daughters.

42
00:05:21.890 --> 00:05:23.390
And yet. where is he now?

43
00:05:24.020 --> 00:05:25.930
Send another raven that he can understand.

44
00:05:26.195 --> 00:05:28.370
One may have with drawings rather than
letters.

45
00:05:34.490 --> 00:05:35.490
What word from Harrenhal?

46
00:05:38.450 --> 00:05:42.370
If Vhagar does not come. our defenses will
not hold.

47
00:05:48.550 --> 00:05:50.040
Do not be disheartened. Darren.

48
00:05:51.710 --> 00:05:53.340
Your brother will join us soon.

49
00:05:58.670 --> 00:06:00.510
Why seize Tumbleton?

50
00:06:01.090 --> 00:06:02.290
It's no stronghold.

51
00:06:02.490 --> 00:06:03.530
It's a market town.

52
00:06:04.310 --> 00:06:05.410
Its lord is meek.

53
00:06:05.580 --> 00:06:06.830
Its walls are poorly defended.

54
00:06:07.490 --> 00:06:09.910
Hightower may as well paint a rondel on
his chest.

55
00:06:10.170 --> 00:06:10.390
Why?

56
00:06:11.805 --> 00:06:13.630
Does he mean to somehow win their support?

57
00:06:16.300 --> 00:06:20.290
He dares me to rain fire down on a seat
that raised my banner.

58
00:06:21.010 --> 00:06:23.470
And the realm would name me Maegor
returned.

59
00:06:23.795 --> 00:06:25.010
They'd rise up against me.

60
00:06:25.640 --> 00:06:29.350
And the same gods who delivered me to the
throne would rightly cast me down.

61
00:06:30.040 --> 00:06:30.930
If I may.

62
00:06:32.460 --> 00:06:35.790
Your grace. Prince Daemon's river host
marches on King's Landing.

63
00:06:36.790 --> 00:06:38.110
Tumbleton is not much further.

64
00:06:39.090 --> 00:06:41.510
If his men were to go there instead...

65
00:06:41.510 --> 00:06:41.730
Hmm.

66
00:06:42.010 --> 00:06:43.750
It would not be bloodless.

67
00:06:44.440 --> 00:06:47.050
But it would be far more merciful than
sending dragons.

68
00:06:49.620 --> 00:06:53.230
We march on the town and root out the
Hightowers house to house.

69
00:06:55.370 --> 00:06:56.430
It's a good scheme.

70
00:06:57.730 --> 00:06:58.810
Send orders to Lord Tully.

71
00:07:01.210 --> 00:07:02.410
All while...

72
00:07:04.110 --> 00:07:09.670
For as long as you remain loyal and
useful. you may take your place at my

73
00:07:09.770 --> 00:07:12.030
council and retain the title of Grand
Maester.

74
00:07:16.310 --> 00:07:19.240
The castle's ravens remain your charge.
but the Lady Messiah is to be kept

75
00:07:19.240 --> 00:07:20.540
informed of the comings and goings.

76
00:07:21.560 --> 00:07:22.040
Ah!

77
00:07:24.100 --> 00:07:24.580
Relics.

78
00:07:25.730 --> 00:07:26.480
Of a dead regime.

79
00:07:29.620 --> 00:07:31.700
It will take the rivermen weeks to reach
Tumbleton.

80
00:07:32.610 --> 00:07:34.260
Let us send a dragon to keep vigil.

81
00:07:35.160 --> 00:07:39.260
A woman may have the town under siege.
but he shall not leave except I remove

82
00:07:39.260 --> 00:07:39.540
him.

83
00:07:40.240 --> 00:07:44.880
In the meantime. we have urgent matters at
home.

84
00:07:45.220 --> 00:07:48.120
We have secured some small store of oil
for the market. but...

85
00:07:48.120 --> 00:07:48.680
Where is the hand?

86
00:07:51.465 --> 00:07:52.500
Gods. this council's thin.

87
00:07:58.750 --> 00:08:00.190
Name a master of coin.

88
00:08:01.720 --> 00:08:04.130
The people who soon discover are lacking
resources.

89
00:08:05.480 --> 00:08:06.650
They can blame him.

90
00:08:11.515 --> 00:08:13.200
Investigate Ser Torrin Manderley.

91
00:08:14.240 --> 00:08:14.960
He's intrigued me.

92
00:08:15.920 --> 00:08:18.240
If he's fit. let the gold be his concern
as well as Daemon's.

93
00:08:20.200 --> 00:08:22.700
Mine shall be Ormund Hightower.

94
00:08:26.600 --> 00:08:27.560
I know him as well as you.

95
00:08:29.180 --> 00:08:30.180
I doubt that.

96
00:08:31.480 --> 00:08:32.780
Viserys warded your son to him.

97
00:08:32.880 --> 00:08:33.460
I've never met the man.

98
00:08:35.609 --> 00:08:37.860
I knew him very little.

99
00:08:38.589 --> 00:08:39.460
A long time ago.

100
00:08:40.094 --> 00:08:43.000
After my father took me to court.
I rarely saw Old Town.

101
00:08:43.020 --> 00:08:43.740
Tell me what you do know.

102
00:08:50.050 --> 00:08:51.710
He sees himself as a scholar.

103
00:08:53.139 --> 00:08:54.110
He studies the histories.

104
00:08:54.630 --> 00:08:56.270
He collects tapestries.

105
00:08:56.690 --> 00:08:57.330
Writes ballads.

106
00:08:58.270 --> 00:08:59.810
Despises the ignorant and uncouth.

107
00:09:01.649 --> 00:09:03.730
When we were young. Gwaine thought him
cruel. but...

108
00:09:04.120 --> 00:09:04.970
Gwaine thought that of many.

109
00:09:05.879 --> 00:09:06.790
How is he with Derham?

110
00:09:09.510 --> 00:09:10.330
Fatherly. I'm told.

111
00:09:11.819 --> 00:09:13.590
Derham's only a babe when he took him to
ward.

112
00:09:18.929 --> 00:09:21.790
Did it pay new to have to send your child
away?

113
00:09:26.460 --> 00:09:27.460
It's my choice.

114
00:09:29.120 --> 00:09:29.680
Why?

115
00:09:34.489 --> 00:09:38.570
I bore Viserys three Targaryens.

116
00:09:40.279 --> 00:09:44.390
But with the last. my last. I wanted him
to be a Hightower.

117
00:09:47.089 --> 00:09:50.630
In truth. I'm glad I waged that battle.
seeing now what came of our other sons.

118
00:09:51.939 --> 00:09:55.190
Perhaps sending Derham away was my truest
act of motherhood.

119
00:09:58.449 --> 00:10:01.050
Though I do not know now what fate that
choice has consigned him.

120
00:10:09.514 --> 00:10:10.820
You know I would have spared him.

121
00:10:21.639 --> 00:10:23.540
He has a sensitivity to odours.

122
00:10:25.940 --> 00:10:26.460
Ormond.

123
00:10:28.759 --> 00:10:29.600
A very strong one.

124
00:10:32.500 --> 00:10:33.300
My Lord Hand.

125
00:10:34.249 --> 00:10:36.460
The Queen has requested your presence of
her small council.

126
00:10:36.840 --> 00:10:37.620
I'm her hand.

127
00:10:38.160 --> 00:10:39.120
Not her mouth.

128
00:10:39.739 --> 00:10:41.300
Leave the talking to those who relish it.

129
00:10:41.979 --> 00:10:43.140
Shall I return with this message?

130
00:10:43.719 --> 00:10:44.580
That you refuse the Queen?

131
00:10:44.780 --> 00:10:46.780
Rather that I serve more effectively.

132
00:10:48.009 --> 00:10:49.800
Her strength lies in dragons now.

133
00:10:50.299 --> 00:10:51.840
She has less need of a man of the sea.

134
00:10:54.719 --> 00:10:57.400
But my son shall attend her in my stead.

135
00:10:57.720 --> 00:10:58.700
You certainly look the part.

136
00:11:00.929 --> 00:11:02.420
I am not a creature of the court.

137
00:11:02.965 --> 00:11:04.100
I don't know what I'm doing.

138
00:11:05.269 --> 00:11:06.860
There is great opportunity for you there.

139
00:11:09.009 --> 00:11:09.980
I cannot give you legitimacy.

140
00:11:10.939 --> 00:11:13.120
But I can give you the chance to better
yourself.

141
00:11:18.514 --> 00:11:20.550
Anger is not something that could be ended
with a blade.

142
00:11:21.070 --> 00:11:21.730
My Lord.

143
00:12:39.370 --> 00:12:40.150
I'm here.

144
00:12:42.610 --> 00:12:43.430
I'm here.

145
00:12:47.660 --> 00:12:47.820
I'm here.

146
00:12:48.094 --> 00:12:49.280
It's a penny to touch the dragon.

147
00:12:52.439 --> 00:12:53.740
Nothing's free in these woods.

148
00:12:54.979 --> 00:12:56.780
You can sit the saddle for a half-grove.

149
00:12:57.139 --> 00:12:58.060
Touch will suffice.

150
00:12:58.900 --> 00:12:59.620
Thank you.

151
00:13:05.699 --> 00:13:06.370
You seek shelter.

152
00:13:07.299 --> 00:13:07.990
Which way do Rooks rest?

153
00:13:09.239 --> 00:13:10.690
He's got both hands on him.

154
00:13:11.050 --> 00:13:12.170
Just two touches.

155
00:13:30.989 --> 00:13:32.040
What's wrong with your leg?

156
00:13:37.539 --> 00:13:38.610
You can kill a man of the faith.

157
00:13:39.554 --> 00:13:40.910
For a few pennies if you wish.

158
00:13:42.799 --> 00:13:44.630
Though I doubt the gods would look kindly
upon it.

159
00:13:45.299 --> 00:13:46.430
You don't look like a septon.

160
00:13:47.330 --> 00:13:48.090
He's alive.

161
00:13:53.120 --> 00:13:53.920
I know it.

162
00:13:54.520 --> 00:13:55.320
He's alive.

163
00:13:55.460 --> 00:13:56.040
He must be.

164
00:14:00.100 --> 00:14:01.220
I'm here.

165
00:14:01.940 --> 00:14:03.060
I'm here.

166
00:14:03.140 --> 00:14:03.620
I'm here.

167
00:14:03.840 --> 00:14:04.360
I'm here.

168
00:14:08.440 --> 00:14:09.480
What's he saying?

169
00:14:11.419 --> 00:14:12.340
I'm here.

170
00:14:13.100 --> 00:14:14.100
I'm here.

171
00:14:14.280 --> 00:14:14.900
I know you're alive.

172
00:14:14.980 --> 00:14:15.980
We must hurry no longer.

173
00:14:16.320 --> 00:14:17.180
The danger is great.

174
00:14:17.819 --> 00:14:18.960
I am very sorry.

175
00:14:20.229 --> 00:14:22.120
But you must accept what is before you.

176
00:14:26.429 --> 00:14:27.340
You wanted to see him.

177
00:14:28.129 --> 00:14:28.820
You've seen him.

178
00:14:30.100 --> 00:14:30.960
He's dead.

179
00:14:31.220 --> 00:14:31.600
No.

180
00:14:32.940 --> 00:14:34.840
Will you stay and rot with him?

181
00:14:36.150 --> 00:14:37.520
Will you get up?

182
00:14:38.499 --> 00:14:39.280
And live?

183
00:15:55.699 --> 00:15:56.380
Are you lost?

184
00:16:02.229 --> 00:16:03.260
Where is the castellan?

185
00:16:06.080 --> 00:16:07.000
Slain.

186
00:16:08.669 --> 00:16:09.820
He who succeeds him then?

187
00:16:11.580 --> 00:16:12.500
Slain.

188
00:16:13.709 --> 00:16:15.360
And the one who succeeds him as well.

189
00:16:16.320 --> 00:16:17.500
And who are you?

190
00:16:19.400 --> 00:16:21.380
A steward of a sort.

191
00:16:22.669 --> 00:16:23.740
It's the best you can do at the moment.

192
00:16:24.310 --> 00:16:25.300
This is the hand of the king.

193
00:16:26.729 --> 00:16:27.780
We seek the Prince Aemond.

194
00:16:30.139 --> 00:16:31.620
As I'm sure do many.

195
00:16:35.719 --> 00:16:36.920
He was meant to meet us here.

196
00:16:38.029 --> 00:16:40.340
If you know where he is. I'd advise you to
be forthcoming.

197
00:16:41.480 --> 00:16:42.060
Hm.

198
00:16:46.169 --> 00:16:47.040
He was here.

199
00:16:48.244 --> 00:16:51.380
He seized the castle after Prince Daemon
abandoned it.

200
00:16:51.539 --> 00:16:55.200
But when he learned that Rhaenyra took
King's Landing. he and his dragon fled.

201
00:16:55.250 --> 00:16:56.980
When Rhaenyra took King's Landing?

202
00:17:02.840 --> 00:17:03.820
Oh. my.

203
00:17:05.729 --> 00:17:06.540
Oh. you didn't know.

204
00:17:13.039 --> 00:17:14.700
You've scoured the area. my Lord Hand.

205
00:17:15.029 --> 00:17:18.060
There is sign of a large dragon nest that
has been abandoned.

206
00:17:19.659 --> 00:17:22.040
Prince Aemond may indeed have fled.

207
00:17:32.909 --> 00:17:33.890
King's Landing has fallen.

208
00:17:34.550 --> 00:17:35.250
Aegon is dead.

209
00:17:35.999 --> 00:17:37.330
Our queens are both in chains.

210
00:17:37.879 --> 00:17:41.870
And we are here. alone. with a meager army
and no dragon.

211
00:17:44.249 --> 00:17:45.630
We have the enemy just where we want them.

212
00:17:49.054 --> 00:17:50.100
Aemond would not desert me.

213
00:17:50.200 --> 00:17:51.060
And yet he's not here.

214
00:17:52.020 --> 00:17:52.640
Is he?

215
00:17:55.044 --> 00:17:56.600
Let us send a raven to Tumbleton.

216
00:17:57.799 --> 00:18:02.140
Alert my cousin of this news. and our
intent to join our strength to his.

217
00:18:02.969 --> 00:18:05.560
Ormond is a stiff-necked windbag.
but he's neither craven nor stupid.

218
00:18:06.399 --> 00:18:07.760
He will have some canny plot of foot.

219
00:18:11.780 --> 00:18:12.220
No.

220
00:18:18.829 --> 00:18:20.990
The game is played. Ser Criston.
and it is lost.

221
00:18:22.159 --> 00:18:24.090
What possible profit is there in pursuing
it?

222
00:18:28.979 --> 00:18:31.660
You know. Balilk. conceived this all a
great game. don't you?

223
00:18:32.119 --> 00:18:34.540
To win. to lose. or go home to a feather
bed.

224
00:18:34.540 --> 00:18:34.900
Ah.

225
00:18:36.714 --> 00:18:37.580
I was a foot soldier.

226
00:18:37.860 --> 00:18:38.520
Did you know that?

227
00:18:39.140 --> 00:18:39.760
Steward's son.

228
00:18:40.934 --> 00:18:44.440
All my father had was at the pleasure of
Lord Dondarrion when his favour failed or

229
00:18:44.440 --> 00:18:45.540
we had melted away.

230
00:18:49.159 --> 00:18:50.640
My father died of sorrow.

231
00:18:51.829 --> 00:18:53.820
There is no home for one like me.

232
00:18:56.714 --> 00:18:58.320
Not while Rhaenyra sits the throne.

233
00:19:01.999 --> 00:19:02.960
Our task is simple.

234
00:19:04.879 --> 00:19:06.620
Keep the river scum from reaching King's
Landing.

235
00:19:06.919 --> 00:19:08.280
Give Ormond time to swell his ranks.

236
00:19:08.889 --> 00:19:10.920
Their army is ten times our size.

237
00:19:11.200 --> 00:19:11.240
Twenty.

238
00:19:12.559 --> 00:19:13.580
But let us attack it.

239
00:19:14.629 --> 00:19:16.320
As the scorpion does the ox.

240
00:19:19.439 --> 00:19:20.680
Let us become Wraiths.

241
00:19:21.649 --> 00:19:24.380
With fear as our standard. strike from the
quiet and the darkness.

242
00:19:24.699 --> 00:19:26.380
Our fight will not be clean. but it will
be pure.

243
00:19:28.459 --> 00:19:29.340
We'll be man to man.

244
00:19:32.809 --> 00:19:34.020
And it will be free from dragons.

245
00:19:39.690 --> 00:19:40.170
Ser Edgar!

246
00:19:40.954 --> 00:19:42.110
We will delay them at most.

247
00:19:44.290 --> 00:19:45.890
Not change their course.

248
00:19:46.030 --> 00:19:46.550
Perhaps not.

249
00:19:47.789 --> 00:19:49.090
But it is as you said. Sergwayne.

250
00:19:49.709 --> 00:19:50.770
We must cling to our honour.

251
00:19:51.434 --> 00:19:52.750
Lest we become beasts ourselves.

252
00:20:17.900 --> 00:20:18.820
Who goes there?

253
00:20:19.569 --> 00:20:20.680
Alan. of Hull.

254
00:20:20.980 --> 00:20:21.760
I'll see him.

255
00:20:22.340 --> 00:20:22.740
Come.

256
00:20:24.620 --> 00:20:25.480
Your Grace.

257
00:20:27.209 --> 00:20:31.760
Lord Corlys has ridden out by the Dragon
Gate to hunt the Triarchy raiders that

258
00:20:31.760 --> 00:20:32.440
plague our trade.

259
00:20:34.529 --> 00:20:36.640
He has able men who could lead that
campaign.

260
00:20:37.740 --> 00:20:41.540
While his queen struggles to restore a
broken kingdom.

261
00:20:46.159 --> 00:20:47.820
Your Grace. if I may.

262
00:20:49.614 --> 00:20:55.000
My Lord Father has lost much and found
himself thwarted.

263
00:20:56.154 --> 00:20:59.300
A fight is perhaps what he needs.

264
00:21:06.700 --> 00:21:07.180
No.

265
00:21:08.799 --> 00:21:09.960
My father's life's work.

266
00:21:11.069 --> 00:21:12.760
A recreation of the seat of Old Valyria.

267
