The price keeps rising and you can't keep
up.

361
00:28:14.150 --> 00:28:15.430
Tell them. for everyone.

362
00:28:16.110 --> 00:28:16.810
Hear that?

363
00:28:17.870 --> 00:28:18.450
Drinks!

364
00:28:18.710 --> 00:28:19.230
For everyone!

365
00:28:25.910 --> 00:28:27.230
That one broke my...

366
00:28:27.230 --> 00:28:27.990
The attack of the system.

367
00:28:28.590 --> 00:28:28.870
What is this?

368
00:28:28.890 --> 00:28:30.190
What is this?

369
00:28:32.569 --> 00:28:34.650
You said your men were honorable.

370
00:28:34.930 --> 00:28:36.210
This one has sinned.

371
00:28:39.289 --> 00:28:41.210
I was billeted at the smithy. my lord.

372
00:28:41.410 --> 00:28:42.190
But the smith.

373
00:28:43.049 --> 00:28:43.730
He didn't like it.

374
00:28:44.469 --> 00:28:46.410
Mayhaps he resents the imposition.

375
00:28:47.539 --> 00:28:49.610
Or mayhaps he is loyal to Rhaenyra.

376
00:28:50.759 --> 00:28:51.530
But he struck me.

377
00:28:51.730 --> 00:28:52.230
My lord.

378
00:28:53.219 --> 00:28:55.190
If it please you. we bear you no ill will.

379
00:28:55.410 --> 00:28:56.390
But this man...

380
00:28:56.889 --> 00:28:58.130
...went to ravish my sister...

381
00:28:58.130 --> 00:29:00.150
...and then broke my wife's arm when she
tried to stop him.

382
00:29:00.829 --> 00:29:01.610
She is a weaver.

383
00:29:02.769 --> 00:29:04.090
We need what little she earns.

384
00:29:05.350 --> 00:29:06.330
Is this true?

385
00:29:06.830 --> 00:29:07.730
No. my lord.

386
00:29:07.890 --> 00:29:08.250
Liar!

387
00:29:08.290 --> 00:29:09.310
Look at this woman's arm!

388
00:29:09.410 --> 00:29:10.130
She attacked me!

389
00:29:10.189 --> 00:29:11.750
Is there no safety in her arms?

390
00:29:11.750 --> 00:29:12.430
She called me a cunt!

391
00:29:12.430 --> 00:29:13.530
I will have calm!

392
00:29:18.450 --> 00:29:19.430
What is your name?

393
00:29:19.899 --> 00:29:20.930
Garrick. my lord.

394
00:29:21.290 --> 00:29:22.170
Of Whitegrove.

395
00:29:22.879 --> 00:29:24.470
Garrick of Whitegrove.

396
00:29:25.999 --> 00:29:27.270
You have violated guest right.

397
00:29:28.499 --> 00:29:30.370
You have debauched yourself upon a
woman...

398
00:29:30.370 --> 00:29:31.290
...and injured another.

399
00:29:32.359 --> 00:29:33.830
Your punishment will fit your crime.

400
00:29:34.329 --> 00:29:35.130
You will be gelded.

401
00:29:36.190 --> 00:29:36.730
And...

402
00:29:36.979 --> 00:29:38.770
...you will have your own arm broken.

403
00:29:39.139 --> 00:29:40.590
You may remain in my service...

404
00:29:40.590 --> 00:29:41.730
...but trespass again...

405
00:29:41.730 --> 00:29:42.570
...and you will hang.

406
00:29:42.750 --> 00:29:43.230
My lord!

407
00:29:44.030 --> 00:29:45.110
I have a wife!

408
00:29:46.250 --> 00:29:47.270
My lord!

409
00:29:47.590 --> 00:29:47.870
No!

410
00:29:48.410 --> 00:29:49.330
See them home.

411
00:29:49.859 --> 00:29:51.190
Have a maester tend to their wounds.

412
00:29:56.990 --> 00:29:58.490
We must keep a firm grip.

413
00:29:59.369 --> 00:30:00.430
Tensions are high.

414
00:30:01.629 --> 00:30:04.110
Lawlessness and disorder claw at our gate.

415
00:30:04.750 --> 00:30:05.530
Yes. sir.

416
00:30:15.890 --> 00:30:19.870
I wish to see all correspondence between
the Red Keep and Ormond Hightower since my

417
00:30:19.870 --> 00:30:20.510
father's death.

418
00:30:21.070 --> 00:30:21.870
Your grace.

419
00:30:25.144 --> 00:30:29.130
How much control do the Hightowers exert
over the Faith?

420
00:30:29.979 --> 00:30:33.110
Well. they endowed the building of the
Starry Sept.

421
00:30:34.219 --> 00:30:37.950
And Oldtown was their seat for.
well. centuries before the Conquest.

422
00:30:39.219 --> 00:30:43.350
The Seven are as intrinsic to the
Hightower fabric as. well. dragons are to

423
00:30:43.350 --> 00:30:44.170
House Targaryen.

424
00:30:44.170 --> 00:30:45.630
But control?

425
00:30:45.930 --> 00:30:46.790
I think not.

426
00:30:47.050 --> 00:30:49.730
The Faith is too proud to allow such
influence.

427
00:30:52.029 --> 00:30:54.330
The High Septon has refused to anoint me.

428
00:30:57.209 --> 00:30:59.950
The Faith clings tightly to its separate
powers.

429
00:31:03.079 --> 00:31:09.430
If I may be so bold to ask. your grace.
does it matter?

430
00:31:10.239 --> 00:31:11.650
Your grace hits the throne.

431
00:31:12.079 --> 00:31:14.950
Your people have welcomed you back as a
liberator.

432
00:31:15.189 --> 00:31:16.450
Your dragons rule the skies.

433
00:31:16.510 --> 00:31:19.150
Are these not symbols of power enough?

434
00:31:20.970 --> 00:31:23.070
Perhaps I could remove him.

435
00:31:23.239 --> 00:31:27.930
The Monarch has ever had some influence in
the naming of the High Septon.

436
00:31:28.050 --> 00:31:33.250
But to remove him altogether would surely
incite the Faith. and therefore the

437
00:31:33.250 --> 00:31:33.790
Faithful.

438
00:31:36.234 --> 00:31:41.890
Unless you were considering a more
permanent removal.

439
00:31:44.509 --> 00:31:46.000
I never thought you were so bloodthirsty
or well.

440
00:31:46.959 --> 00:31:47.620
Rather impressed.

441
00:31:48.220 --> 00:31:49.000
Alas. no.

442
00:31:49.989 --> 00:31:51.740
Bring Ormond's letters once you have
collated them.

443
00:31:52.174 --> 00:31:55.220
There's been no word from Prince Daemon on
his progress.

444
00:31:55.639 --> 00:31:56.960
None as yet. Your Grace.

445
00:32:03.119 --> 00:32:05.910
I thought never to see you in the Vale
again. Prince Daemon.

446
00:32:07.279 --> 00:32:09.550
What after the tragic death of your first
wife.

447
00:32:11.579 --> 00:32:15.290
And yet I receive raven after raven from
my bannermen. informing me of your

448
00:32:15.389 --> 00:32:16.810
progress throughout my domain.

449
00:32:16.810 --> 00:32:17.670
Hmm.

450
00:32:18.699 --> 00:32:20.810
Time heals even the deepest of wounds.

451
00:32:23.239 --> 00:32:25.810
I am most delighted to return.
my lady.

452
00:32:28.579 --> 00:32:31.810
And who could ever fail to be charmed by
your... warmth?

453
00:32:33.389 --> 00:32:34.290
But I mustn't tarry.

454
00:32:34.559 --> 00:32:36.790
You promised the crown men in return for a
dragon.

455
