You had your dragon. yet we have no men.

456
00:32:42.329 --> 00:32:43.470
I should send babes.

457
00:32:44.610 --> 00:32:47.550
Prince Joffrey's dragon was years away
from being large enough to defend the

458
00:32:47.550 --> 00:32:47.750
Vale.

459
00:32:48.009 --> 00:32:49.330
And Rhaenyra took even that away.

460
00:32:50.329 --> 00:32:54.450
A less forbearing person might have seen
the crown's offering as an insult.

461
00:32:54.550 --> 00:32:55.450
A pledge is a pledge.

462
00:32:55.799 --> 00:32:58.850
It was my understanding that the war was
won. my prince.

463
00:32:59.669 --> 00:33:02.330
What need does she have of more soldiers?

464
00:33:04.390 --> 00:33:05.270
In truth...

465
00:33:06.889 --> 00:33:08.730
I have not come for men. I've come for
gold.

466
00:33:09.230 --> 00:33:09.670
Huh.

467
00:33:10.259 --> 00:33:11.450
So your coffers are empty.

468
00:33:11.679 --> 00:33:13.150
Oh. the work of Hightower treachery.

469
00:33:13.319 --> 00:33:16.610
But perhaps a generous offering of coin
would demonstrate your...

470
00:33:17.889 --> 00:33:19.030
...fealty to the crown.

471
00:33:19.879 --> 00:33:22.810
Prince Daemon Targaryen. standing in my
high hall.

472
00:33:23.689 --> 00:33:24.910
A beggar with a tin cup.

473
00:33:25.370 --> 00:33:25.470
Hm.

474
00:33:27.459 --> 00:33:29.170
I never thought I'd live to see such a
sight.

475
00:33:29.350 --> 00:33:32.410
A gift of gold would offer you the benefit
of my speedy departure.

476
00:33:38.610 --> 00:33:39.290
Very well.

477
00:33:49.300 --> 00:33:50.400
Which one?

478
00:33:50.980 --> 00:33:51.440
Well because of.

479
00:33:51.440 --> 00:33:52.320
Hey.

480
00:33:56.560 --> 00:33:57.480
Why?

481
00:33:57.660 --> 00:33:58.580
Why?

482
00:33:59.400 --> 00:34:00.320
Why?

483
00:34:05.770 --> 00:34:05.790
Why?

484
00:34:05.790 --> 00:34:06.470
Why?

485
00:34:07.310 --> 00:34:08.230
Why?

486
00:34:08.230 --> 00:34:08.370
Why?

487
00:34:08.630 --> 00:34:08.810
Why are you waiting for those?

488
00:35:10.460 --> 00:35:12.450
There are these two trên walls that we
have to stand out.

489
00:35:36.510 --> 00:35:37.350
Wren.

490
00:35:57.930 --> 00:35:58.770
Lakiri?

491
00:36:00.050 --> 00:36:00.790
Lakiri!

492
00:36:10.960 --> 00:36:12.680
What have you done to yourself?

493
00:36:18.720 --> 00:36:19.560
How?

494
00:36:22.960 --> 00:36:24.340
I fed him sheep.

495
00:36:28.940 --> 00:36:31.120
Rhaenyra believes this dragon and his
rider are the reason.

496
00:36:33.620 --> 00:36:34.360
Jace is dead.

497
00:36:39.800 --> 00:36:40.660
I wanted only to help.

498
00:36:40.800 --> 00:36:41.060
No.

499
00:36:41.740 --> 00:36:42.420
To show her.

500
00:36:42.500 --> 00:36:43.060
To show you.

501
00:36:43.670 --> 00:36:44.820
I... I never intended...

502
00:36:46.340 --> 00:36:47.140
Does she suffer?

503
00:36:47.260 --> 00:36:48.680
From breaking me. dearie!

504
00:36:51.430 --> 00:36:52.520
Jade Arryn knows you are here.

505
00:36:53.300 --> 00:36:55.100
You were meant to accompany my sons to
Pentos.

506
00:36:55.220 --> 00:36:55.860
They are well attended.

507
00:36:56.060 --> 00:36:56.660
They will be saved.

508
00:36:56.760 --> 00:36:58.000
You swore to be their guardian.

509
00:36:58.160 --> 00:36:58.700
And do what?

510
00:37:01.250 --> 00:37:02.740
Teach them to be ladies of the realm.

511
00:37:04.620 --> 00:37:05.840
I would be of no use there.

512
00:37:06.890 --> 00:37:08.180
Just as I was of no use here.

513
00:37:11.950 --> 00:37:12.820
If you go now.

514
00:37:13.640 --> 00:37:14.760
To where you are meant to be.

515
00:37:14.980 --> 00:37:15.880
Rhaenyra need not know.

516
00:37:16.100 --> 00:37:16.900
We will find a ship.

517
00:37:17.020 --> 00:37:17.800
Leave the dragon behind.

518
00:37:18.900 --> 00:37:20.360
I will not save him.

519
00:37:20.520 --> 00:37:21.840
He is not like the others. Rhaenyra.

520
00:37:21.920 --> 00:37:22.460
He is wild.

521
00:37:22.640 --> 00:37:23.440
He cannot be trusted.

522
00:37:23.660 --> 00:37:24.200
He is mine.

523
00:37:25.130 --> 00:37:25.980
He is a part of me.

524
00:37:27.240 --> 00:37:29.200
I have been alone all my life.

525
00:37:31.390 --> 00:37:33.100
The Targaryen without a dragon.

526
00:37:34.000 --> 00:37:35.360
Disregarded or...

527
00:37:35.360 --> 00:37:35.960
Or worse.

528
00:37:36.820 --> 00:37:37.280
Pitied.

529
00:37:39.660 --> 00:37:42.780
Can you yourself say you ever gave me more
than a passing thought?

530
00:37:43.500 --> 00:37:44.480
Rhaenyra the unfortunate.

531
00:37:47.250 --> 00:37:48.560
Rhaenyra the least among your children.

532
00:37:52.420 --> 00:37:54.200
Come back with me then to King's Landing.

533
00:37:54.320 --> 00:37:54.460
No.

534
00:37:54.860 --> 00:37:55.640
We will...

535
00:37:57.120 --> 00:37:58.140
Speak to her together.

536
00:37:58.360 --> 00:37:59.500
We will tell her it was a mistake.

537
00:37:59.620 --> 00:38:02.620
How can I ever stand before her again
after what I have done?

538
00:38:04.740 --> 00:38:05.580
No. I can never return.

